    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a block of mass 2 m in a sled of mass m that is on a horizontal surface. The sled is attached to one end of a spring with constant k, and the other end of the spring is attached to a wall.\" src=\"/images/4f5c005208558c2aad32983902070c81.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A sled of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> is attached to one end of a horizontal spring with spring constant <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"k\"><math alttext=\"k\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>k</mi></math></span></span>, as shown. The other end of the spring is attached to a wall. The sled is free to move along a horizontal surface with negligible friction. A block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 m\"><math alttext=\"2 m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> is placed in and secured to the sled. The sled-block system is displaced a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x sub 0\"><math alttext=\"x sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> and then released. Which of the following expressions is equal to the time the sled-block system takes to travel a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"8 x sub 0\"><math alttext=\"8 x sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>8</mn><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
